properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 16 at 5:16AM AKST until January 16 at 6:00PM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
The National Weather Service in Juneau has issued a High Wind
Warning, which is in effect until 6 PM AKST this evening.

* WHAT...North winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts around 60 mph.

* WHERE...Downtown Haines, Lutak Inlet, Tanani, and Mud Bay.

* WHEN...Until 6 PM this evening.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds may blow down trees and power lines.
Loose objects will be blown around. Travel will be difficult,
especially for high profile vehicles.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Winds have gusted around 60 mph early
Thursday morning. So far, there have been no reports of damage.
properties.instruction:
A high wind warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected
or occurring.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM AKST THIS EVENING
